Job Summary

We are looking for an experienced Project Manager to lead Digital Projects within the banking industry.

Mandatory Skill-set
• Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering or other related disciplines;
• Minimum 6-9 years of Project Management experience managing complex digital projects;
• Strong experience in end-to-end project delivery lifecycle and software development lifecycle;
• Excellent stakeholder engagement and interpersonal skills;
• Proactive and independent worker who is able to work well under tight deadlines.

Desired Skill-set
• Experience in the banking industry;
• PMP-certified.

Responsibilities
• Manage delivery of Digital Projects with a medium to high complexity as Product Delivery Lead;
• Collaborate with business and technology stakeholders including external vendors to identify enhancements, ensure end-to-end process delivery and optimize customer journey;
• Develop and analyze Business Requirements and translating requirements... into Business Requirements Documents/User Stories;
• Review Functional Specifications Documents and Narratives to ensure specifications are in line with Business Requirements;
• Lead a team of Test Analysts and Test Automation Engineers;
• Provide post-implementation support including user training, problem management and resolving of customer issues according to Service-Level Agreements.

Should you be interested in this career opportunity, please send in your updated resume to apply@sciente.com at the earliest.

When you apply, you voluntarily consent to the disclosure, collection and use of your personal data for employment/recruitment and related purposes in accordance with the SCIENTE Group Privacy Policy, a copy of which is published at SCIENTEs website (https://www.sciente.com/privacy-policy).

Confidentiality is assured, and only shortlisted candidates will be notified for interviews
